              <a href="/holidays/st-patricks-day" class="sa-hol-btn">St. Patrick's Day</a>
            </div>

            <div class="sa-scripture-box">
              <p class="sa-scripture-label">&#9656; What Scripture Says</p>
              <p><strong>Deuteronomy 12:30–32</strong> — "You shall not worship Yahuah your Elohim in that way; for every abomination to Yahuah which He hates they have done to their gods... Whatever I command you, be careful to observe it; you shall not add to it nor take away from it."</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── FINAL WORD ── -->
    <section class="sa-final">
      <div class="sa-final-inner">
        <p class="sa-final-label">&#8213; Final Word &#8213;</p>
        <div class="sa-prose">
          <p>
            Sun worship is not a relic of the ancient world. It is alive. Its symbols stand in the Vatican, in Washington, and in London. Its theology is encoded in Freemasonry and transmitted through its members into government, law, finance, and culture. Its festivals are the holidays the entire world celebrates. Its sexual expression is the dominant cultural force of our age. And its obelisks — the phallus of the sun god — stand as monuments in the most powerful cities on earth, hidden in plain sight.
          </p>
          <p>
            Yahuah saw this coming. He warned about it. He condemned it. He told His people to tear it down, burn it, and walk away from it. And He provided an alternative: His appointed times (Leviticus 23), His calendar (Exodus 12:2), His worship (in spirit and in truth, John 4:24), and His Son, Yahushua the Messiah, who is the <strong>true light</strong> of the world (John 8:12) — not the sun.
          </p>
          <p>
            Salvation comes through Yahushua alone, by grace through faith (Ephesians 2:8–9). Once saved, we walk in His commandments out of love (John 14:15). That walk means coming out of the system — out of its holidays, out of its symbols, out of its calendar, and out of its version of "love" and "light."
          </p>
        </div>

        <blockquote class="sa-final-quote">
          <p>"Come out of her, my people, lest you share in her sins, and lest you receive of her plagues."</p>
          <cite>— Revelation 18:4</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </section>

